cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically multiscale image classification, and proposes a new neural network architecture for achieving scale-equivariant representations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the model complexity and computational burden, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks and numerical experiments suggest a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the improved deformation robustness of the proposed method, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the interpretability of the proposed method, which suggests a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia).
